<p class="govuk-body-s govuk-!-margin-top-1 govuk-!-margin-bottom-0" style="color:#505a5f;">
  Rules run for each CMDB service offering during <strong>bulk sync from CMDB</strong> (below). Use <strong>Import from Excel</strong> to bulk-update phase and product URL from a FIPS completion export.
  Status rules: the first active match sets Rejected or Retired (inactive).
  Enterprise rules set <strong>Mark as enterprise service</strong> to Yes when matched (for example <strong>ServiceClassification</strong> contains <code>Business Service</code>).
  Rejection defaults come from legacy Strapi sync (<code>applyRejectionCriteria</code>): title contains <code>(PP)</code> and excluded parent categories.
  Retired products in Compass are skipped on bulk sync; single-product sync can still update them after reactivation.
</p>
